title: Adaptation.
overview: A lovelorn screenwriter becomes desperate as he tries and fails to adapt 'The Orchid Thief' by Susan Orlean for the screen.

title: Barfi!
overview: Three young people learn that love can neither be defined nor contained by society's definition of normal and abnormal.

title: OMG: Oh My God!
overview: A shopkeeper takes God to court when his shop is destroyed by an earthquake.

title: Zelig
overview: "Documentary" about a man who can look and act like whoever he's around, and meets various famous people.

title: Good Bye Lenin!
overview: In 1990, to protect his fragile mother from a fatal shock after a long coma, a young man must keep her from learning that her beloved nation of East Germany as she knew it has disappeared.

title: Happiness
overview: The lives of several individuals intertwine as they go about their lives in their own unique ways, engaging in acts society as a whole might find disturbing in a desperate search for human connection.

title: Chhichhore
overview: A tragic incident forces Anirudh, a middle-aged man, to take a trip down memory lane and reminisce his college days along with his friends, who were labelled as losers.

title: Harvey
overview: Due to his insistence that he has an invisible six foot-tall rabbit for a best friend, a whimsical middle-aged man is thought by his family to be insane - but he may be wiser than anyone knows.

title: Badhaai ho
overview: A man is embarrassed when he finds out his mother is pregnant.

title: Ferris Bueller's Day Off
overview: A high school wise guy is determined to have a day off from school, despite what the Principal thinks of that.

title: Le dîner de cons
overview: A few friends have a weekly fools' dinner, where each brings a fool along. Pierre finds a champion fool for next dinner. Surprise.

title: Clerks
overview: A day in the lives of two convenience clerks named Dante and Randal as they annoy customers, discuss movies, and play hockey on the store roof.

title: The Hangover
overview: Three buddies wake up from a bachelor party in Las Vegas, with no memory of the previous night and the bachelor missing. They make their way around the city in order to find their friend before his wedding.

title: Young Frankenstein
overview: An American grandson of the infamous scientist, struggling to prove that his grandfather was not as insane as people believe, is invited to Transylvania, where he discovers the process that reanimates a dead body.

title: Vizontele
overview: Lives of residents in a small Anatolian village change when television is introduced to them

title: Jeux d'enfants
overview: As adults, best friends Julien and Sophie continue the odd game they started as children -- a fearless competition to outdo one another with daring and outrageous stunts. While they often act out to relieve one another's pain, their game might be a way to avoid the fact that they are truly meant for one another.

title: Yeopgijeogin geunyeo
overview: A young man sees a drunk, cute woman standing too close to the tracks at a metro station in Seoul and pulls her back. She ends up getting him into trouble repeatedly after that, starting on the train.

title: Charade
overview: Romance and suspense ensue in Paris as a woman is pursued by several men who want a fortune her murdered husband had stolen. Whom can she trust?

title: Manhattan
overview: The life of a divorced television writer dating a teenage girl is further complicated when he falls in love with his best friend's mistress.

title: Office Space
overview: Three company workers who hate their jobs decide to rebel against their greedy boss.
